ailable.\n\n6. Look at the git log for recent commits to see what loop 16 actually changed.\n\nBe very thorough - I need to know exactly which of the 3 issues from the codex completer verdict were fixed in loop 16 and which remain.","agentId":"aa44849bef8c8bfc8","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile my findings:\n\n## Summary of ralph-burning-rewrite Loop 16 Status\n\nBased on my thorough investigation of the codebase, git history, loop artifacts, and completion verdicts, here is the exact status:\n\n### Loop 16 Scope\n\nLoop 16 was intended to complete the daemon automation layer with:\n1. Watcher/issue-ingestion capability\n2. Requirements handoff path (both quick and draft modes)\n3. Fix the broken `SC-PROJ-009` conformance scenario\n\n### All 3 Issues from Loop 15's Codex Verdict: **FIXED**\n\n#### Issue 1: `SC-PROJ-009` Conformance Fixture (FIXED)\n- **Status**: Line 680 in `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs`\n- **Fix**: The fixture now correctly includes `\"stage_cursor\":{\"stage\":\"planning\",\"cycle\":1,\"attempt\":1,\"completion_round\":1}` in the active_run object\n- **Evidence**: This is the canonical shape required by the schema; the scenario properly validates that deleting a project with an active run fails\n\n#### Issue 2: Daemon Dispatch into Requirements (FIXED)\n- **Status**: Lines 371-385 in `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs`\n- **Implementation**:\n  - `process_task()` now checks `task.dispatch_mode` with a match statement before claiming lease/worktree\n  - `DispatchMode::RequirementsQuick` → calls `handle_requirements_quick()` which:\n    - Invokes requirements quick service\n    - Links the run_id to the task\n    - Derives the seed handoff\n    - Updates task metadata and switches to `Workflow` mode\n    - Falls through to project/workflow dispatch in the same cycle\n  